Happy thanksgiving everyone 🦃🍁 is it too early for a christmas tree? 😂🙈 This year Im not posting a picture with gordo (he’s snoring next to me, don’t worry!) because this has been a special year and I’m truly thankful for friends and our life in this country. Coming from a broken home and a broken country I never really thought it would be possible to make real connections anywhere. In my heart, I always felt that anything good would always be taken away, that’s how I grew up. So this year I’m so thankful for each and everyone of you, that have opened your hearts to us, two immigrants with nothing, and really showed us how wonderful life can be. I’m so thankful to have so many people in my life who I love and call friends, even the most unexpected ones. Thank you for changing my life, thank you for teaching me how much fun it can be when you just enjoy the moment and thank you for helping me pick up the pieces even when you didn’t realize you did 💕🥺 I love you all!!
PD: Also thankful for burrito because he’s the best dog ever. 😜

I would say this is our thanksgiving mood but I would be lying 😂🙈 This is our always mood 😂😂😂 Had the best time last night and currently Black Friday shopping! Dont miss out on the big sales also happening on @clubmar right now 😍😍😍
